%I A185092 #25 May 13 2026 08:55:14
%S A185092 1,2,3,4,6,12
%N A185092 Divisors of 12.
%C A185092 Numbers k such that j^j == j^j^j (mod k) for every j. For k <= 16, we can compute membership directly (see Mathematica code). For k > 16, we have j = 2 as a counterexample. - _Eric M. Schmidt_, Aug 03 2014
%H A185092 Sunil K. Chebolu and Michael Mayers, <a href="https://doi.org/10.4169/math.mag.86.2.143">What is special about the divisors of 12?</a>, Mathematics Magazine, 86 (2013), 143-146.
%t A185092 h1[mod_] := Table[PowerMod[i, i, mod], {i, 1, mod + LCM[mod*CarmichaelLambda[mod]]}]; h2[mod_] := Table[PowerMod[i, i^i, mod], {i, 1, mod + LCM[mod*CarmichaelLambda[mod]]}]; Union[Table[If[h1[i] == h2[i], Print[i]; i], {i, 1000}]]
%Y A185092 Cf. A217290, A323383.
%K A185092 nonn,fini,full,changed
%O A185092 1,2
